Business Briefs
ACC Corp.'s Danbury Cellular Telephone subsidiary
completed a $3 million purchase of the license and assets to
operate a cellular radio telephone system in a rural Kentucky
area from Petry Television Inc., N.Y.
   ---
   Unocal Corp. said it will begin phasing out motor fuel
marketing through dealers and marketers in the Southeast by
allowing existing fuel supply contracts to expire.
   ---
   BankAmerica Corp. acquired Valley Capital Corp., which
operates Valley Bank of Nevada and Caliber Bank in Arizona.
Under the agreement, each of Valley Capital's 10 million
shares will be exchanged for about 0.9 share of BankAmerica
common stock, valuing the transaction at about $440 million.
   ---
   Unilever N.V. said it will buy the minority interest in
its Turkish subsidiary currently held by Turkiye Is Bankasi
A.S., a Turkish bank company.
   ---
   Continental Medical Systems Inc. and Healthtrust Inc. plan
to build an $11 million medical rehabilitation hospital in
Terre Haute, Ind.
   ---
   California Microwave Inc. said it agreed to acquire
privately held Microwave Radio Corp., a Boston maker of
microwave radios. Terms weren't disclosed.
   ---
   ICF International Inc. said a unit was awarded a
three-year, $5.3 million contract by the Interior Department
to study air quality problems in the Gulf of Mexico.